Pattern Recognition

📌 Binary Search Tree

📌 Tree Traversal

Key Observation:

Unlike a normal binary tree,

a BST lets us eliminate half the tree at every step using node values.

------------------------------------------------------------

Interview Insight

The trick is to use the BST property.

You never need to search both subtrees.

If both nodes lie on the same side,

move there.

Otherwise,

you've found the point where their paths diverge,

which is the Lowest Common Ancestor.
